items.content: We need this reply by early Monday if possible!!

Hi Osayd,

Apologies for the delay! Unfortunately this ticket fell through the cracks and was just assigned to me now.

There are two approaches we can take, either

  • Submitting a request to Transfer Pixels across Buisness Center (Recommended)
    • The client will have full ownership and control of their Pixels 
    • Drawback is that another Athena ticket will have to be made on our Internal TPS platform to start the process (~1 week)

  • Using the Pixel Sharing function to share the existing Pixels from the Dentsu BC to the new Client owned BC 
    • The client will be easily able to do this on their own
    • Drawback is that the Dentsu BC must remain active and the Pixels will still remain in the Dentsu BC


1) Recommended approach - Submit an Internal TPS ticket to Transfer Pixels Across Business Centers. This will ensure that the client has full control of the Pixel moving forward. Further details and steps can be found here: https://bytedance.larkoffice.com/docx/VuIoduNsxo3TjZxe2xZc2pWRnsh 

  • Note, the Athena Ticketing Platform is going to be different than the one you used here to submit an Implementation Ticket:
    • Internal TPS Athena Ticketing link: https://ads.tiktok.com/athena/requester/boards?identify_key=ce513cc7f78be06846c87f202dc42fd824b0323b7d53872079291faf4d4f7456
    • Please select Buisness Center > Pixel Sharing
  • Sales contact to submit an Athena ticket first using the information above and get in touch with one of the scaled TPS members, so that the TPS team can record the case, conduct preliminary research, and escalate the issue accordingly. Please provide all the necessary information so that we can process your ticket:
    • Advertiser name
    • BC ID (BC owning the pixel)
    • Pixel Id (make sure there are no duplicate pixel codes shared by the sales team)
    • Receiving BC ID
    • Receiving BC user admin (email and UID)
  • HQ team will not process email requests without a submitted Athena ticket.
  • In the ticket, sales contact to specify the reason why your client needs to transfer the pixel and Who the transferer and transferee are
  • Process will take roughly ~1 week

2) Pixel Sharing: https://ads.tiktok.com/help/article/pixel-sharing-business-center?lang=en

  • The client is able to do this themselves but as mentioned above, the drawback here is that the Dentsu BC must remain active and the Pixels will still remain in the Dentsu BC
  • The client will still own the Pixel as it is theirs to begin with, but partial control will still remain with Dentsu as the Pixels will still remain in the Dentsu BC, being shared out to the client's new BC


Thanks for your patience and understanding here, Osayd!

Best,

Robbie
